reviewText: This is one of Lash's best movies: decent direction, a really strong supporting cast, and a wicked finale. Unfortunately, it's too painful to watch in this version. The black and white contrast is so extreme that features disappear from people's faces, a white horse running down a dusty road can't be seen, and any action taking place in a shadow, such as under a tree or a covered sidewalk. is hidden in blackness.
Not a great western but it's very nostalgic and entertaining. It was great to see LaRue having his whip duel with El Azote!
